dct_title_s: The South-Polar regions [cartographic material] : to illustrate the paper by Staff-Commander J. E. Davis / [engraved by] Edwd. Weller.
dct_description_sm: Relief shown by hachures and spot heights. Depth shown by soundings. Routes, dates, and directions of expeditions between 1772 and 1859 are shown. Known and conjectural portions of Antarctic coast and areas of ice are shown. From: Journal of the Royal Geographical Society of London. Vol. 39 (1869), pp. 91-5; held in Firestone Library. Call number: G7 .J687 Another copy of this map is held in Special Collections : Historic Map Collection. Call number: HMC01.6570 Map of Antarctica showing place names and exploration routes and tracks. Relief shown by hachures and spot heights. From: The journal of the Royal Geographical Society of London, 1869.
dct_publisher_sm: London: published for the Journal of the Royal Geographical Society by John Murray, Albemarle St., 1869.
London : Published for the Journal of the Royal Geographical Society, by J. Murray, Albemarle Street, 1869.
